node.text:
Whether you're a new mom, an expecting mom, a mom of two or more children, or can’t become/decided against becoming a mother and are therefore celebrating your own mother today -  we wish you a HAPPY MOTHER'S DAY!

It is a crazy and demanding but wonderful journey and very unique for every single mother. This is why we asked Jennifer, our brand ambassador, to share with us her thoughts and memories about her first months of being a mom. We want to invite all of you to share your thoughts as well! 

How has your life changed? 
What would you say to the moms to be and the ones considering becoming a mom?

@thejeneralist: "Becoming a mother is one of the craziest things you can do in life. It's a selfless act of love that requires you to temporarily put aside you own needs and place that focus on somebody else.
You learn quickly to adjust to the roller coaster of emotions that are full of each day, reminding yourself to cherish each passing moment.
You become a student all over again as your child becomes your greatest teacher. And in the same breath your greatest friendship.
Becoming a mother has been the greatest challenge I've faced in life but it's also been the most rewarding experience I've been privileged to have." 

#mothersday #mom #momtobe #momtobeagain #momslifebelike

During night-time:
- Nothing hanging when Willow is sleeping at night to avoid any safety risk
- Bed placed under the baby monitor to be able to check how little Willow's doing

During daytime:
- Using the crib interchangingly as a bassinet, moving it to the living room or wherever Willow is taking her daytime naps

How are you using your Stokke Sleepi?

#BabySleep #SleepingRoutine #BabyCrib #BabyBed #StokkeSleepi #NewMom
Sleepi Design: Susanne Grønlund & Claus Hviid Knudsen

node.text:
We have the pleasure of sharing this wonderful shot starring @lisahahnbueck that can be seen in @voguegermany - we love it!

Not only does Lisa look stunning, she also has a great message for moms and women out there: "becoming a mom, staying a woman: The first thing I had to learn to keep the balance between my own personality and my family, is to never measure myself against the super-powers of other women. At the same time, it’s equally important to give other mothers and families their space to find out what kind of parents they want to be. To never judge. Just let be. In other words, every mom, every child, and all of their needs are different. They can never be compared to each other. I had to teach this very valuable lesson to myself. So I am here to tell you to free yourself from the judgement of others. But especially your own. If you take care of your own needs once in a while, you will be more balanced and maybe even a better mom." 📸: @lisahahnbueck

#sotrue #motherhood #newmom #xploryx

Our designers are committed to creating products that have one thing in commong: CONNECTION AT THE CORE 

From interpreting your reactions and facial expressions, to retreating to you as a safe haven; your baby’s experience of the world is shaped by how they share it with you. We want children to get the most out of life. To move, reach out, touch, explore, and learn as much as possible with joy and security through connection with you. 

That's why out Stokke Xplory X is height adjustable, to bring your baby closer to you for bonding, connection and eye contact so your baby can always search the reassurance from you while you explore this super exciting new world together. 

Learn more by tapping our picture! 📸: @mrs_mamaa
